@node Intro "Introduction"

Flam is a fire generator.

It's de result of the work with another member of Ringard : Noël Butterlin.

It's been compiled with SAS/C 6.55

The first algorithm came from PovRay 1.0. It has been greatly enhanced
for maximum speed.

If you like RayTracing, flam is made for you !


Pictures are generated virtualy in 24bits ans saved in IFF ByteRun0


Advantages are :

	- The size of the drawn picture is only limited by the amount of
	available memory.

	- Pictures are very precise and can be used in mapping.

@endnode

@node Compatibilite "Compatibility"

Flam needs at least KickStart 2.0, 512 Ko of free memory and @{"Reqtools.library" link merci}
in drawer LIBS:
68000 version needs MathTrans.library
FPU versions need MathIEEEDoubTrans.library


Warning !
---------

For confortable using, you should have a FPU and FAST memory.

@endnode

