@node doc
Flam exists in several @{"versions" link vs}. Each version use the
characteritics of the configuration concerned by.


Flam has only one window. Each function can be accessed per shortcut or per
mouseclick.

	1°) @{"Fire parameters" link flamme}

	2°) @{"Screensize" link ecran}

	3°) @{"Others" link comm}


Yes but I have @{"PROBLEMS" link pbm}

@endnode

@node flamme "The Flamme"

Ratio_X/Y :

	It defines the amount of horizontal/vertical place that the flame
	takes in the screen.

Turbulence :

	If this value is large, the flame will look yielding.

Octave :

	It defines the depth in applying turbulence.
	If this value is great, the flame will look like real.
	Too big value are not necessary.

Time :

	This parameter is used only if you make animations. It's the time
	interval between two images measured in 1/100 of sec.



Yes but I have @{"PROBLEMS" link pbm}
@endnode

@node comm "START and SAVE Gadgets"


By clicking on START a window will open, displaying the percentage of
the picture already drawn. At the end, the picture will be automaticly
saved. 

CloseWindow stops the computation.


The number of images, with the @{"TIME" link flamme} gadget, enables you to create
your own animation.




Yes but I have @{"PROBLEMS" link pbm}
@endnode

@node pbm "Common problems"


0) What ? I made a mistake, I've no problems.


1) Merci. This is well done, but I can't execute FracPro.

You NEED @{"Reqtools.library" link Compatibilite} in LIBS: and @{"Kickstart 2.0" link Compatibilite}
Look what the different @{"versions" link Compatibilite} need.


2) Yes, but it NEVER packs !!.

You don't have enough memory. Actually, FracPro needs a big buffer to compress.
It'll be changed in next versions.





